episode_title: 901 - The One Where No One Proposes

content.description: Rachel’s Room, Joey moves Ross’s coat to get the tissues Rachel wants and the engagement ring box Mrs. Geller gave him falls out of the pocket it was inside. Joey goes to one knee, picks up the box, opens it, and sees that it’s an engagement ring.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Joey.
(He turns to face Rachel on one knee with the box open.)

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh my God. (Pause) Okay.
(Joey is stunned.)
[Cut to Ross getting of an elevator carrying a bouquet of flowers and walking down the hall to Rachel’s room.]
[Cut back into Rachel’s room.]

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: So uh…I guess we should…make it official huh?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Uh… Look Rach…(Ross enters.) Hey Ross is here! Hey look! It’s my good friend Ross. Hey Ross.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Hey Joey. (To Rachel) Hey you.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Hey you.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Hey and look he brought flowers. Thanks Ross, but I’m really more of a candy guy. (Laughs.)

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: You’re weird today. (He turns to Rachel and Joey puts the ring back.) (To Rachel) Listen I uh, wanted to talk to you about something.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Uh yeah, actually I kinda need to talk to you too.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Uh Joey, can you give us just a minute?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: No.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: What?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Oh, I’m sorry. I meant no.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Hi! Hey look who’s here!
content.parenthetical: entering with everyone else including Mr. Geller

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: Where’s my granddaughter? I’ve been practicing my magic tricks.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: He pulled a quarter out of my ear!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Hey, where’s uh, where’s mom?

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: She went to pick up Aunt Liddy.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Oh, Aunt Liddy’s coming? That means we get five dollars each!

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: So when do I get to meet Emma and show her this? (Pulls a bouquet of flowers out of his sleeve.)

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Okay. Wow.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Uh Dad, Emma’s in the nursery. I’ll take you now. If you want, but (To Rachel) I really want to talk to you.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I know, I still need to talk to you.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Oh hey but, before you guys do that (To Rachel) I need to talk to you, and Ross, I need to talk to you.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh and I need to talk to you.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: About what?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: To see if know what these guys are talking about.

content.description: Outside the Nursery, everyone but Rachel is standing and looking into the window.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Isn’t she beautiful?

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: Look at her, my first grandchild.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: What about Ben?

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: Well of course Ben, I meant my first granddaughter. (To Monica, mouths) Wow.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Have umm, have you thought anymore about you and Rachel?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Oh well yeah, actually I was going to talk to her when you guys all came in the room.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Yay! It’s so exciting! Wow, you could’ve done that with us there.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Yeah right.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh sure okay, you can touch yourself in front of us but you can’t talk to Rachel.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: What?! When have I ever touched myself in front of you guys?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh please! Just before when you were asleep in the lounge! That Armenian family was watching you instead of the TV. Oh, that reminds me. That Mr. Hasmeje still has my Gameboy .

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Hey Chandler, can I talk to you for a second?

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Sure.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Dude I just did something terrible.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: That was you?! I thought it was Jack!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: No! No, that was Jack! Rachel thinks I asked her to marry me!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: What?! Why does she think that?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Because it kinda looked like I did.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Again, what?!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Okay well, I was down on one knee with the ring in my hand…

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: As we all are at some point during the day.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: It wasn’t my ring! It fell out of Ross’s jacket! And when I knelt down to pick it up Rachel thought I was proposing!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Ross had a ring?! And he was gonna propose?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: I guess.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: And you did it first?! This is gonna kill him! You know how much he loves to propose!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: I know! I know it’s awful.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Well, what did she say?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: She said yes.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Does Ross know?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Oh God, what the hell am I going to tell him?

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Well maybe you don’t have to tell him anything.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Oh, I like that. Yeah…

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: If you clear things up with Rachel then Ross never needs to find out, but you have to do it now before he hears about it and kicks your ass!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Now let’s not get carried away. (He walks away as Monica comes over and hugs Chandler from behind.)

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: I want a baby.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Honey, we’ve been over this. I need to be facing the other way.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Come on! Come on, if we have sex again it’ll double our chances of getting pregnant. Do you think that closet’s still available?

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: I’m so tired. (She starts kissing him.) Yeah okay, but no foreplay.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Deal!
[Back in front of the nursery window.]

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Dad seriously! Y’know you really should see someone about that!

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: Noted.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: I wanna go talk to Rachel for a minute, are you gonna be okay alone for a bit?

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: Are you kidding me, I could stay and look at her forever.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Actually umm… (He turns Mr. Geller’s head to look at Emma.)

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Hey!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Hi.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Are you all right?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Uhh… I think I just got engaged.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh my God! He did it?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Well…did you know he was gonna ask me?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Are you kidding? I’m like the one who talked him into it. I like to think of myself as the puppet master of the group.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: And you really think this is a good idea?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: I just talked him into it, don’t tell me I have to do you too. The puppet master gets tired people.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I just don’t know! It just doesn’t feel right.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Why?! You two are so meant to be together, everybody thinks so.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Really?! Even Ross?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Especially Ross!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Oh uh, hey Pheebs. Uh y’know what? I’ll-I’ll come back later. (He goes to leave but runs into Ross who’s entering.)

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Wow! Kind of uh, kind of a full house here. I’ll guess just…I’ll come back. (Ross exits followed by Joey.)

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: There he goes, your fianc�e.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I guess so.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Although he does play with himself in his sleep.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I can’t say that I’m surprised.

content.description: A hallway, Joey and Ross find Mr. Geller with his ear up against a janitor’s closet door.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Dad, what are you doing?

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: I think there are people in there having sex.
(Ross turns to look at Joey.)

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: It can’t be me, I’m standing right here.

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: Wanna peek?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: No!

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: Come on!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Y’know what? I don’t like you without mom. (To Joey) Come on. (Walks away.)

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: We’re not peeking? (Follows him.)

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: Well I’m peeking. (He peeks.) Oh my God!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Hello sir, you know Monica.

content.description: Rachel’s Room, she is taking the ring out of Ross’s jacket, looks at it, and puts it on her finger as Joey enters.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Hey uh, is it okay to come in?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Of course! Oh Joey, this ring I…it’s beautiful I love it!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Yeah uh look Rach, there’s something I gotta tell ya.
(There’s a knock on the door and a nurse enters carrying Emma.)

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Hey!

content.speaker: Nurse
content.text: Hey! Are you ready to try nursing again?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yeah! Hi Emma. Hey, why do you think she won’t take my breast?

content.speaker: Nurse
content.text: It’s all right honey, it takes some babies a while to get it, but don’t worry. It’ll happen.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Yowsa! (Looks away.)

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Okay sweetie, you can do it. Just open up and put it in your mouth.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Dear Lord.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I’m sorry honey, what were you saying?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Oh uh-uh yeah, I think that…

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh look, she’s pulling away again! Do you think my nipples are too big for her mouth? (Joey gets embarrassed.) She looks scared. Doesn’t she look scared?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Y’know, I don’t really know her.

content.speaker: Nurse
content.text: Why don’t we try massaging the breast to stimulate the flow. (Does so.)

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Are you kidding me?!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: It’s just so frustrating! Why doesn’t she want my breast?!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: I don’t know! Maybe she’s crazy! (Storms out.)

content.description: The Lobby, Ross is eating a sandwich as Phoebe rushes up to him.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh hey! Wait up!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Hi!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Congratulations! I didn’t want to say anything in front of Joey ‘cause I didn’t know if he knew yet.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: What, that we had a baby? Come on let’s give him a little credit, although, he did eat a piece of plastic fruit earlier.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: No! No, that you and Rachel are engaged!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: What?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh, it’s a secret. Oh goodie! Yes! We haven’t done the secret thing in a long time.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Phoebe, there is no secret. Okay? I didn’t propose.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Are you lying? Is this like that time you tried to convince us that you were a doctor?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: I am a doctor! Y’know what? I’m just gonna go and talk to Rachel myself.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: All right, me too. (They go into her room and see that she’s sleeping.) Should we wake her up?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: No! No, come on let her sleep! She’s so exhausted.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: And so engaged. (Points to the ring that Rachel is wearing.)

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: What? (Motions for Phoebe to go outside with him.) Oh my God! She-she thinks we’re engaged! Why? Why? Why would she think we’re engaged?!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Perhaps because you gave her an engagement ring? Y’know Ross doctors are supposed to be smart.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: I didn’t give her that ring!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Really?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: No!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: So whose ring is it?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: It’s mine.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Is it an engagement ring?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Yes!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: But you didn’t give it to her?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: No!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: But you were going to propose?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: No!!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Huh, I might be losing interest in this.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Look. Look, my mom gave me that ring because she wanted me to propose to Rachel, but all I wanted to do is if she maybe…kinda…wanted ah…start…things up again.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh, what beautiful lukewarm sentiment.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Look, I didn’t want to rush into anything. And it seemed like she didn’t want to either. But I don’t, I don’t understand how any of this happened! What? Did she find the ring in my jacket, assume that I was going to propose, throw it on, and-and just start telling people?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: No! No, she said you actually proposed to her.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Well I didn’t! I didn’t propose! (Pause) Unless uh… (Pause) Did I? I haven’t slept in forty hours and…it does sound like something I would do.

content.description: The Janitor’s Closet, Chandler and Monica are trying to figure out what to do now.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Look, we can’t stay in here forever.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Oh, I still can’t believe my dad saw us having sex! He didn’t make it to one of piano recitals, but this he sees!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: This is okay. We’re all adults here; there’s nothing to be ashamed of. Now, let’s put our underwear in our pockets and walk out the door. (They do so and find Mr. Geller leaning against a wall stunned.)

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Hi Dad! I can still call you that right?

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: Of course. I’ll always be your dad.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: I just want you to know that what you witnessed in there, that wasn’t for fun.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: It wasn’t fun?!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Why? Why-why-would you—Wh-why… (To Mr. Geller) Look, I just don’t want you to think that we’re animals who do it whenever we want.

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: Oh, I don’t think that. Before today I never thought of you two having sex at all. It was a simpler time.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: The truth is, Dad, we’re-we’re trying.

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: What?

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Yeah, we’re trying to get pregnant.

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: Oh my God! This is so exciting! Well, get back in there! (Points to the closet) I’ll guard the door!

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Well, that’s okay dad, we-we can wait until later.

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: Whoa-whoa-whoa! I don’t think so! Aren’t you ovulating?

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Daddy?!

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: Well you gotta get at it princess! When your mother and I were trying to conceive you, whenever she was ovulating, bam, we did it. That’s how I got my bad hip.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: That’s funny, this conversation’s how I got the bullet hole in my head.

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: This one time I had my knee up on the sink and your mother, she was…

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Daddy! I don’t think we need to hear about the specific positions you and mom had sex.

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: You’re right, you’re right. This is about your positions. Now, what I saw in the closet is not the optimum position for conceiving a child, although it might feel good.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: I don’t feel good right now.

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: But pleasure is important, (To Chandler) and it helps if the woman has an orgasm. You up to the task sailor?

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Seriously sir, my brains? All over the wall.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Hey.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Hey. I need to tell you something.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Well, now’s a good time. I’m on my way to have my ears cut off.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Joey asked me marry him.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: What?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Joey proposed to me.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Is he crazy?! You just had Ross’s baby!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Well, I-I said yes.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: What?! Are you crazy? You just had Ross’s baby! It’s-it’s so inappropriate. No, it’s worse than that. It’s wrong. It’s… It is bigger than mine! (Rachel’s engagement ring.)

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I know. Days of Our Lives , thank you very much.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: You can’t marry him!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Why not? I don’t want to do this alone! And he’s such a sweet guy and he loves me so much.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Well do you love him?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Sure.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Sure?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yeah, I mean whatever.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Honey, the question is…do you really want to marry Joey?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: No. No, I don’t. Could you be a dear and go tell him?

content.description: A Hallway, Chandler is following Joey.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: You still haven’t told Rachel you weren’t really proposing?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: No! She had the ring on, she seemed so excited, and then she took her breast out.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Joey, you have to tell her what’s going on! And what did it look like?!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: I didn’t look at it. Stupid baby’s head was blocking most of it.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Go and tell Rachel right now before Ross finds out.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Look, it’s not that easy. She said she wanted to marry me. I don’t want to hurt her.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Okay, look, just do it gently.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: You’re right. You’re right. I-I’ll go tell her now before Ross finds out and I’ll be gentle. I can do that. I am a gentle person. Oh, by the way. Two people screwing in there (Points to the closet Chandler and Monica were in) if you want to check that out.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Hey.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Hey.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Listen, I um… I heard about the engagement.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Surprised?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: And confused. Rach, sweetie, I-I um…I didn’t propose to you.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I know.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: I don’t think you do.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: You didn’t propose to me. Joey did.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Poor baby, you’re so tired. Rach, I didn’t propose to you, Joey didn’t propose to you, and Chandler didn’t propose to you.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Uh… You didn’t propose to me, Chandler didn’t propose to me, but Joey did.
(Joey enters.)

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Joey proposed to you?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: I can come back.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Hey, wait! Wait-wait-wait! Joey, did you propose to her?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: No.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yes you did!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Actually, technically, I didn’t.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Well then why did you give me a ring?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Wait! Whoa-whoa, you…you gave her the ring?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: No! No, and I did not ask her to marry me!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yes, you did!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: No, I didn’t!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yes, you did!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: No, I didn’t!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yes, you did! And don’t you say, “No, I didn’t!”

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Ahhh!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: He was right there. He got down on one knee and proposed.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Whoa! You were down on one knee?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Yeah. Yeah, that looks bad. But I didn’t…I didn’t propose!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Then what did happen?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yeah, what did happen?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Okay, the ring fell on the floor and I went down to pick it up and you thought I was proposing.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yeah, but you said, “Will you marry me?”

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: No, I didn’t!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yes, you did!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: No, I didn’t!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yes, you did—Oh my God you didn’t! (Screams) Well then why didn’t you tell me that before?!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Well I tried, but people kept coming in and then you took your breast out!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Whoa! Hey! Whoa-whoa-whoa, you saw her breast?!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: I’ll tell you about it later. Be cool.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Well then Joey, what the hell were you doing with an engagement ring?!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: It wasn’t my ring! It’s Ross’s ring! That’s why I felt so bad Rach, because he was going to propose.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: What?!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: You were gonna propose to me?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Uhh… No.
(An awkward silence follows.)

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Well, this is awkward. {See? I told you so.}

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: But I-I was going to see if y’know, maybe you uh, start dating again but that—I mean that-that was all, Rach.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Dude, step up! I proposed.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: No, you didn’t!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Oh that’s right. There’s a lot going on here and I think I ate some bad fruit earlier.
(There’s a knock on the door and the Nurse enters carrying Emma.)

content.speaker: Nurse
content.text: Hey, she just woke up! She’s hungry. Why don’t we give this another try?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Okay.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: I can’t believe you told her I was going to propose!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: I can’t believe you’re not going to propose!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Hey, I’m not going to rush into anything!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Oh yeah, dude, I totally understand. Usually after I have a baby with a woman I like to slow things down!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh my God!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: What?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: She’s doing it Look, she’s breast-feeding look!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Ah, it’s beautiful.

content.speaker: Nurse
content.text: I’ll come back for her later.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Okay.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Thank you. (The nurse exits.)

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh wow, this feels weird.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Good weird?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Wonderful weird.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Y’know what you guys? I’m uh, I’m gonna go too. And uh, I’m sorry about everything.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Honey don’t worry, it was my mistake.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: No, Rach, I should’ve told you sooner. It’s just that…Man! That kid is going to town! (Joey makes his awkward exit.)

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: She’s perfect.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: We’re so lucky.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: We really are.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Look, I-I know it’s not a proposal and I don’t know where you are, but with everything that’s been going on and with Emma and…I’ve been feeling…

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I know. I know. I’ve feeling…

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Yeah?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yeah. (Laughs nervously)

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Okay, well, that… Wow, okay, well, umm…then maybe, at least we can, we can talk about us again.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yeah, maybe.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Well good, okay. I-I, kind of think y’know if we…if… You’re wearing the ring.
(Pause.)

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Wh-what’s that?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: And you told Phoebe you were engaged.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I’m sorry, what?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: When you thought Joey proposed did…did you say yes?

content.description: Outside the Janitor’s Closet, there are people having sex and Mr. Geller is trying to give them some pamphlets.

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: Kids, I spoke to a doctor and picked up this pamphlets on how to get pregnant. (He slides them under the door.)

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Hey dad!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Hey.

content.speaker: Mr. Geller
content.text: Sorry to bother you again, but could you pass my pamphlets back? (They do so.) Thank you.
